WEBVTT

00:00.125 --> 00:01.532
- [Gordon] Tonight on "Hotel Hell,"

00:01.532 --> 00:04.806
I'm trying to breathe life back
into a historic country inn.

00:04.806 --> 00:06.892
You know, it smells like shit.

00:06.892 --> 00:09.884
The hotel's arrogant
owner, Robert Dean II.

00:09.884 --> 00:12.387
- I've always thought you
should live with nice things

00:12.387 --> 00:13.263
if you can afford them.

00:13.263 --> 00:16.047
- Treats the inn like his personal castle

00:16.047 --> 00:18.362
and treats his loyal staff with disdain.

00:18.362 --> 00:20.113
Go on then, you pompous fuck.

00:20.113 --> 00:22.699
- Excuse me, don't talk to me like that.

00:22.699 --> 00:24.263
- Well, what's wrong with it?

00:24.263 --> 00:26.505
Is this hotel beyond my help?

00:26.505 --> 00:29.300
- I'm barely surviving,
financially and emotionally.

00:29.300 --> 00:31.250
- I mean, I'm gonna lose everything.

00:32.392 --> 00:35.260
(dramatic music)

00:50.485 --> 00:53.266
(tiger roaring)

00:57.870 --> 01:00.602
- [Gordon] The historic Juniper
Hill Inn sits on a hilltop

01:00.602 --> 01:03.323
above the quaint village
of Windsor, Vermont.

01:03.323 --> 01:05.346
Built in 1902, the country mansion

01:05.346 --> 01:10.560
boasts 28 luxurious bedrooms
and two grand dining rooms.

01:10.966 --> 01:15.043
- It is filled with original
works of art and antiques,

01:15.043 --> 01:16.847
all museum quality.

01:16.847 --> 01:18.589
- [Gordon] Antiques dealer, Robert Dean II

01:18.589 --> 01:20.288
and his boyfriend, Ari Nikki,

01:20.288 --> 01:22.029
bought the business six years ago.

01:22.029 --> 01:24.438
- I've always thought that you
should live with nice things,

01:24.438 --> 01:25.307
if you can afford them.

01:25.307 --> 01:26.941
- I think it looks good there, Robert.

01:26.941 --> 01:27.962
- I thought you'd like it.

01:27.962 --> 01:30.924
The guests that we don't
want here are people

01:30.924 --> 01:33.207
who don't have a lot of money.

01:33.207 --> 01:34.730
- [Gordon] The inn may look the part,

01:34.730 --> 01:37.211
but despite Robert's dreams
of an elite country estate,

01:37.211 --> 01:39.307
the hotel is barely functioning.

01:39.307 --> 01:42.373
- Robert Dean has no hotel
or no restaurant experience.

01:42.373 --> 01:44.392
- The price is maybe a
little bit high for locals.

01:44.392 --> 01:45.519
- $350?

01:45.519 --> 01:47.625
- Two night minimum, so that's.

01:47.625 --> 01:48.963
- [Both] $700.

01:48.963 --> 01:51.048
- The lack of communication
is very frustrating.

01:51.048 --> 01:52.633
- Where are you?

01:52.633 --> 01:54.249
- I know the customers see that every day.

01:54.249 --> 01:56.387
- I need my key too, because with this one

01:56.387 --> 01:57.570
I can't even get in my room.

01:57.570 --> 01:58.439
- Okay.

01:58.439 --> 01:59.849
- [Gordon] With bookings
at an all-time low,

01:59.849 --> 02:02.038
the hotel is in serious financial trouble.

02:03.196 --> 02:04.718
But that doesn't stop Robert

02:04.718 --> 02:06.418
from living a millionaire's dream.

02:06.418 --> 02:10.112
- Robert believes this
place is his playground.

02:11.900 --> 02:13.320
A playground for his friends.

02:13.320 --> 02:15.622
- We've gotta have a
lot of clothes made by.

02:15.622 --> 02:18.187
(group laughing)

02:18.187 --> 02:22.611
- He comps all their meals and
rooms, but we never get tips.

02:22.611 --> 02:24.415
- They're having a hard time paying me,

02:24.415 --> 02:26.803
because they give away all
of their money and food

02:26.803 --> 02:27.960
to their friends, showing off,

02:27.960 --> 02:29.618
using this as their private castle.

02:29.618 --> 02:31.192
- [Gordon] With hardly any paying guests,

02:31.192 --> 02:33.643
it's no wonder that
this inn is in the red.

02:33.643 --> 02:34.852
- Yes, we are losing money,

02:34.852 --> 02:36.993
more or less like $200,000 a year.

02:37.876 --> 02:39.920
- I think that the
place is gonna be closed

02:39.920 --> 02:41.964
and that's very sad.

02:41.964 --> 02:43.465
- Gordon is gonna come into this place

02:43.465 --> 02:45.623
and say this place is fucked.

02:45.623 --> 02:48.731
- If I don't stop this
business from bleeding money,

02:48.731 --> 02:49.631
it's doomed.

02:51.441 --> 02:54.851
(jaunty music)

02:54.851 --> 02:56.715
I'd love to own an inn
in a setting like this.

02:56.715 --> 03:00.399
If you get it right, you'd
make an absolute fortune.

03:00.399 --> 03:02.237
Before I get to Juniper
hill, I want to find out

03:02.237 --> 03:04.635
what the town's folk
think of their local inn.

03:05.716 --> 03:06.822
- Hello.
- How are you?

03:06.822 --> 03:07.906
- [Shopkeeper] Very well and yourself?

03:07.906 --> 03:09.741
- Yeah, well, I have
been driving all morning.

03:09.741 --> 03:12.275
How's Juniper Hill Inn?

03:12.275 --> 03:14.475
- You're gonna love it, it's beautiful.

03:14.475 --> 03:15.633
- And reputation?

03:15.633 --> 03:18.500
- It tends to be a little on
the high end for our area.

03:18.500 --> 03:21.701
But I would love to have
a place to go to locally.

03:21.701 --> 03:22.848
- Do they not invite locals up there?

03:22.848 --> 03:24.913
- I feel that I'd be interrupting.

03:24.913 --> 03:26.227
I feel like I'd be intruding.

03:26.227 --> 03:27.377
- Oh, really?

03:28.500 --> 03:30.450
What a shame. Thank you so much.

03:30.450 --> 03:32.358
- Have a great day and welcome to Windsor.

03:32.358 --> 03:33.473
- Thank you very much, indeed, take care.

03:33.473 --> 03:35.243
- Enjoy your visit.
- Thank you.

03:37.574 --> 03:39.990
Here we are, Juniper Hill Inn.

03:39.990 --> 03:43.473
Now who in the hell would
bring an RV all the way up here

03:43.473 --> 03:44.995
and not stay in that stunning hotel?

03:44.995 --> 03:45.864
Look at it.

03:47.127 --> 03:49.093
My God, that's beautiful, wow.

03:49.093 --> 03:50.848
Okay, around to the front door.

03:53.744 --> 03:55.005
Can't believe they
haven't cleared the snow

03:55.005 --> 03:56.677
